- Use TypeScript everywhere, strict mode enabled.
- Modular, testable, and clean code.
- Use composables and feature-based structure.
- Write docstrings and comments for all methods.
- Use ESLint, Prettier, and Vitest for linting, formatting, and testing.
- All code must be accessible, maintainable, and scalable.
